---
const showcases = [
  {
    id: 'actemra',
    drug: 'ACTEMRA',
    task: 'T1 Seriousness',
    result: 'SERIOUS: YES',
    resultClass: 'result-serious',
    tokens: 445,
    verdict: '✅ Correct',
    patient: '69-year-old female',
    events: 'Cardiac arrest, Pulmonary embolism, Acute kidney injury, + 11 more AEs',
    thinking: `Pharmacovigilance expert.
Assess seriousness per ICH E2A criteria.
Death (DE), Life-threatening (LT), Hospitalization (HO), Disability (DS), Congenital anomaly (CA).

Patient: 69-year-old female.
Drug: ACTEMRA.
Adverse events: Acute kidney injury, ALT increased, AST increased, Blood glucose decreased, Blood potassium increased, CRP increased, Cardiac arrest, Fibrin D dimer increased, Haemodialysis, Inflammatory marker increased, Platelet count decreased, Pulmonary embolism, Serum ferritin increased, Therapy non-responder.

Outcome: "The patient did not survive the clinical episode." -> Death (DE).
Outcome: "The patient suffered permanent functional limitation." -> Disability (DS).
Clinical severity: Cardiac arrest and pulmonary embolism are life-threatening conditions. -> Life-threatening (LT).
Treatment: Haemodialysis suggests hospitalization or intensive care. -> Hospitalization (HO).

DE (Death): Yes. The patient died.
LT (Life-threatening): Yes. The clinical situation was critical.
HO (Hospitalization): Yes. The severity of the event required hospitalization.
DS (Disability): Yes. Permanent functional limitation is noted.
CA (Congenital anomaly): No. Not applicable.

The case meets multiple seriousness criteria (DE, LT, HO, DS).
Final classification: Serious.`,
    output: `SERIOUS: YES
Criteria met: DE (Death), LT (Life-threatening), HO (Hospitalization), DS (Disability)
Rationale: The clinical outcome meets multiple seriousness categories, confirming serious classification.`,
    why: 'Checks all 5 ICH E2A criteria against 14 adverse events. Identifies 4 criteria met. Zero false positives across 1,027 T1 evaluation samples.',
  },
  {
    id: 'yescarta',
    drug: 'YESCARTA',
    task: 'T4 Causality',
    result: 'WHO-UMC: Possible',
    resultClass: 'result-possible',
    tokens: 541,
    verdict: '✅ Correct',
    patient: '31-year-old female',
    events: 'Cytokine release syndrome (5 days after treatment)',
    thinking: `Pharmacovigilance expert.
Extract evidence and assess causality using WHO-UMC criteria.
31-year-old female. YESCARTA. Follicular lymphoma.
Cytokine release syndrome. 5 days.

Temporal Relationship: The 5-day interval between drug start and event onset is within the expected window for this type of reaction.
Dechallenge: No dechallenge information is available — this key criterion cannot be evaluated.
Rechallenge: The drug was not reintroduced, so rechallenge evidence is absent.
Confounders: No obvious confounders identified between the drug indication and the adverse event.
Alternatives: The adverse event is distinct from the treated condition, reducing confounding risk.
Concomitants: No concomitant medications were reported — the suspect drug is the sole agent.

Temporal: Strong (5 days).
Dechallenge: Unknown.
Rechallenge: Not performed.
Confounders: None.
The evidence is suggestive but not conclusive. The temporal link is strong, but the absence of dechallenge/rechallenge data limits the assessment to 'Possible'.`,
    output: `WHO-UMC Causality: Possible
Evidence:
  - Temporal: Strong (5-day interval, within expected window)
  - Dechallenge: Unknown (key criterion cannot be evaluated)
  - Rechallenge: Not performed
  - Confounders: None identified
  - Alternatives: AE distinct from treated condition
  - Concomitants: Sole agent`,
    why: '6-dimension WHO-UMC evidence extraction. Correctly limits to "Possible" due to missing dechallenge data. 95.5% exact match across 794 T4 evaluation samples.',
  },
];
---

<section class="showcase-section section" id="showcase">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="section-title">See Gemmra <span class="accent-text">think.</span></h2>
    <p class="section-subtitle">Real model outputs with extended thinking traces. Each assessment follows regulatory frameworks (ICH E2A for seriousness, WHO-UMC for causality) — producing the audit trail that pharmaceutical companies and agencies like FDA require.</p>

    <div class="showcase-grid">
      {showcases.map((s) => (
        <div class="showcase-card reveal delay-200">
          <div class="showcase-header">
            <div class="showcase-meta">
              <span class="showcase-task">{s.task}</span>
              <span class="showcase-drug">{s.drug}</span>
              <span class="showcase-tokens">{s.tokens} tokens</span>
            </div>
            <span class={`showcase-verdict ${s.resultClass}`}>{s.result}</span>
          </div>

          <div class="showcase-patient">
            <span class="patient-label">Patient:</span> {s.patient}
            <span class="patient-sep">·</span>
            <span class="patient-label">Events:</span> {s.events}
          </div>

          <details class="showcase-trace" open>
            <summary class="trace-header">
              <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M21 11.5a8.38 8.38 0 0 1-.9 3.8 8.5 8.5 0 0 1-7.6 4.7 8.38 8.38 0 0 1-3.8-.9L3 21l1.9-5.7a8.38 8.38 0 0 1-.9-3.8 8.5 8.5 0 0 1 4.7-7.6 8.38 8.38 0 0 1 3.8-.9h.5a8.48 8.48 0 0 1 8 8v.5z"/></svg>
              Thinking Trace
              <svg class="trace-chevron" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
            </summary>
            <pre class="trace-content"><code>{s.thinking}</code></pre>
          </details>

          <div class="showcase-output">
            <div class="output-header">Structured Output</div>
            <pre class="output-content"><code>{s.output}</code></pre>
          </div>

          <div class="showcase-why">
            <strong>Why this matters:</strong> {s.why}
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .showcase-section {
    background: var(--bg-primary);
  }

  .showcase-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .showcase-card {
    background: var(--bg-secondary);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-card);
    border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
    padding: var(--space-xl);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    transition: transform var(--transition-base), box-shadow var(--transition-base);
  }

  .showcase-card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 24px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
  }

  .showcase-header {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .showcase-meta {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    align-items: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .showcase-task {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    font-weight: 600;
    padding: 3px 10px;
    border-radius: var(--radius-full);
    background: rgba(0, 196, 204, 0.08);
    border: 1px solid rgba(0, 196, 204, 0.2);
    color: var(--accent-primary);
  }

  .showcase-drug {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-heading);
  }

  .showcase-tokens {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .showcase-verdict {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    font-weight: 600;
    padding: 3px 10px;
    border-radius: var(--radius-full);
  }

  .result-serious {
    color: var(--color-error);
    background: rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.08);
    border: 1px solid rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.2);
  }

  .result-possible {
    color: var(--color-warning);
    background: rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.08);
    border: 1px solid rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.2);
  }

  .showcase-patient {
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .patient-label {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .patient-sep {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin: 0 4px;
  }

  .showcase-trace {
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .trace-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-xs);
    padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-md);
    background: rgba(0, 196, 204, 0.04);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--accent-primary);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    cursor: pointer;
    list-style: none;
    user-select: none;
  }

  .trace-header::-webkit-details-marker {
    display: none;
  }

  .trace-chevron {
    margin-left: auto;
    transition: transform 0.2s ease;
  }

  .showcase-trace[open] .trace-chevron {
    transform: rotate(180deg);
  }

  .showcase-trace:not([open]) .trace-header {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .trace-content {
    padding: var(--space-md);
    margin: 0;
    max-height: 220px;
    overflow-y: auto;
    font-size: 11px;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    white-space: pre-wrap;
    word-break: break-word;
  }

  .trace-content code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    background: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .trace-content::-webkit-scrollbar {
    width: 4px;
  }

  .trace-content::-webkit-scrollbar-track {
    background: transparent;
  }

  .trace-content::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb {
    background: var(--border-card);
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .showcase-output {
    background: rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.03);
    border: 1px solid rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.15);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .output-header {
    padding: var(--space-xs) var(--space-md);
    background: rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.05);
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.1);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-success);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
  }

  .output-content {
    padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-md);
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 11px;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--color-success);
    white-space: pre-wrap;
    word-break: break-word;
  }

  .output-content code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    background: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .showcase-why {
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.5;
    padding-top: var(--space-sm);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
  }

  .showcase-why strong {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .showcase-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
